Summary: Strong high pressure will bring rising temperatures, with the potential for excessive heat and high temperatures in the 90s to around 110 degrees. Overnight cooling will be limited, and there will be low relative humidity values, increasing the risk for wildfires. The heat event will peak this weekend, with a moderate to high HeatRisk for inland areas. Cooling will gradually occur through early next week.

Critical weather phenomena: Excessive heat, dangerous heat, limited overnight cooling, low relative humidity, high temperatures, heat advisory, excessive heat warning, HeatRisk, potential for wildfires.